      <h3>Pernambuco</h3>
      <p>Additionally, there are a lot of things to do in the state of Pernambuco. The capital, Recife, has a lot of tourist attractions and a rich culture, that you can experience in the form of its very own type of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forr%C3%B3">music</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frevo">dance</a>, <a href="http://www.buzzfeed.com/gabrielakruschewsky/traditional-brazilian-foods-you-need-to-eat-right-now">food</a> and <a href="http://www.artesanatodepernambuco.pe.gov.br/">art</a>. Next to Recife, there is Olinda, a city founded in 1535, that currently has a gorgeous historic downtown—considered a world heritage site—full of beautiful churches and museums.</p>
